id: llm-call-entry-use-case-attribution
title: Persist use_case on LLMCallEntry through the UsageTracker
scope: feature
owners: [@TODO]
paths:
  - volnix/llm/tracker.py
  - volnix/llm/router.py
surfaces:
  - UsageTracker.record
  - LLMCallEntry (use_case field already exists; just plumbing the value through)
dependencies: [workflow]

intent:
  ``LLMRouter.route(request, engine_name, use_case="default")`` accepts
  a ``use_case`` argument so callers can attribute LLM spend by purpose
  (``"npc_decision"``, ``"agency_personality"``, ``"memory_distill"``,
  ``"world_compiler"``, etc.). The router uses the value for routing
  decisions, but it is dropped before reaching ``LLMCallEntry``: the
  router calls ``self._tracker.record(request, response, engine_name)``
  without passing ``use_case``, and ``UsageTracker.record(...)`` doesn't
  accept it as a parameter. ``LLMCallEntry.use_case`` is already a
  declared field with default ``""`` — the value just never gets there.
  This change adds ``use_case`` as a kwarg on ``UsageTracker.record``
  and threads it through from the router. Three-line plumbing fix; no
  new public surface, no new field, no schema change.

behaviors:
  # UsageTracker
  - ``UsageTracker.record`` MUST accept ``use_case: str = ""`` as a
    keyword-only argument. The default empty string preserves
    backward compatibility for any external caller (none in-tree
    today, but downstream products may construct their own tracker).
  - ``UsageTracker.record`` MUST forward the ``use_case`` value into
    the constructed ``LLMCallEntry``. The argument's value lands
    verbatim on ``LLMCallEntry.use_case`` — no normalization, no
    truncation, no validation beyond what Pydantic does on the
    field today.
  - When ``use_case`` is the empty string (default), the resulting
    ``LLMCallEntry.use_case`` MUST also be the empty string,
    matching the field's existing default. This is the legacy
    pre-attribution behavior.

  # LLMRouter
  - ``LLMRouter.route(...)`` MUST pass its ``use_case`` argument to
    ``self._tracker.record(...)`` as a keyword argument. The router's
    public signature does NOT change.
  - If a route variant calls ``record`` more than once per request
    (retry path), each ``record`` call MUST forward the same
    ``use_case``. (Note: in 0.2.x, ``LLMRouter`` only exposes
    ``route(...)`` and ``embed(...)``; there is no
    ``route_with_tools`` variant. ``embed`` uses
    ``UsageTracker.record_embedding`` which is a separate code path
    OUT OF SCOPE for this TNL — embeddings populate
    ``LLMEmbeddingEntry``, not ``LLMCallEntry``.)

  # LLMCallEntry
  - The ``use_case`` field already exists on ``LLMCallEntry`` with
    default ``""``. This change does NOT modify the entry model.
    Existing rows in the ledger with ``use_case == ""`` remain
    valid; ledger forward-compat (``UnknownLedgerEntry``) is
    untouched.

  # Phase 0 regression oracle
  - Callers that don't pass ``use_case`` (existing in-tree code
    that calls ``router.route(request, engine_name)`` without the
    third positional arg) MUST continue to behave identically.
    The router's ``use_case`` parameter still defaults to
    ``"default"``, so the value flowing into the ledger becomes
    the literal string ``"default"`` for those callers. **This
    is a single-character behavioral delta on the ledger**:
    previously the field was empty string; now it carries the
    router's default value. Phase 0 oracle output that asserts on
    ``LLMCallEntry.use_case`` content (if any) must be updated.

non-goals:
  - No new ``use_case`` constants, no enum, no validation against
    a known set of values. The field is and remains free-form
    ``str`` — callers pick whatever attribution string they want.
  - No backfill of historical ``LLMCallEntry`` rows. Old rows
    stay with whatever they have today (``""`` for entries
    persisted before this change).
  - No retroactive update of in-tree callers to pass meaningful
    ``use_case`` values. Callers that pass ``"default"`` (the
    router's default) keep doing so. Callers can opt into
    attribution incrementally as they touch the call site.
  - No new ledger query helpers (e.g., ``LedgerQueryBuilder.by_use_case``).
    Queries via the existing ``LedgerQueryBuilder.by_payload(...)``
    or raw SQL work; a dedicated builder method is a separate
    decision.
  - No documentation update to ``docs/embedding_volnix.md``'s
    "what's in flux" section. That note about empty ``use_case``
    becomes stale once this lands; updating it belongs in a
    separate documentation pass.
  - No change to ``UsageTracker.record_embedding`` or the
    embedding-specific ledger entry. Embeddings are a separate
    surface.

rationale:
  ``LLMCallEntry.use_case`` was wired as a field on the entry model
  in Phase 4C but the persistence path was never connected. The
  field exists; the router's argument exists; only the kwarg
  forwarding through ``UsageTracker.record`` is missing. Fixing
  this in one TNL keeps the change tight and lets downstream
  consumers (Rehearse, future analytics) build on a populated
  field without first requesting it. The default empty string
  preserves backward compatibility for any consumer who constructs
  their own tracker or calls ``record`` directly.
